# .worktreeinclude.template — Claude Code worktree env-handoff
#
# Copy this file to `.worktreeinclude` in your repo root to opt in.
# On worktree creation, paths matching these patterns are bind-mounted
# (or copied, as fallback) into the new worktree at the same relative path.
# Syntax: gitignore-style fnmatch globs. Blank lines and '#' comments OK.
#
# Note: the resolved `.worktreeinclude` lists paths to secret files.
# If those paths include `.env` or `credentials*`, the existing
# `block-stage-sensitive.sh` hook will refuse to stage them.
# Do not commit the resolved `.worktreeinclude` if it materially differs
# from this template.

# Default entries — uncomment any you want copied into each worktree:
.env
credentials*

# Common optional entries (commented; uncomment as needed):
# .envrc
# .secrets/
# .npmrc
# .pypirc
